  \item What is State X doing to mitigate/adapt?
  \item What might a resident of State X do about climate change?
\end{itemize}

\section{A roll and B roll}

\subsection{A roll}

The A roll is the primary footage that drives the story. It is the main footage that is used to tell the story.

\subsection{B roll}

The B roll is the secondary footage that is used to support the A roll. It is often used to show the viewer what the narrator is talking about.

