\section{Grading Rubric}

\subsection{Self-Grading}

Why self grading on this assignment. As we approach our independent projects, it is important to be able to assess our own work. This is a skill that is important in the professional world. Moreover, each project will be different and I, as the instructor, will not be able to grade each project is unique, making the grading more subjective. 

To build this into the course, I have developed a 3-step process. We will develop the criteria and standards together. Then we'll watch several other projects and develop a range of grades. Finally, you will grade your own project with the context of the criteria, standards, and range of grades.

